                <h2 id="gettingStartedTitle">About MPES</h2>
                <p>
                    The mentors evaluation system within ALX aims to ensure that mentors are delivering high-quality guidance and support to mentees, thereby maximizing the impact of the mentorship program. By evaluating mentors, ALX can identify exceptional mentors, acknowledge their contributions, and provide constructive feedback to enhance their mentoring capabilities.
                    The evaluation process in ALX's mentors evaluation system typically involves multiple components. These may include surveys and assessments completed by mentees, peer evaluations from other mentors, and feedback from program administrators. The evaluation criteria encompass various aspects of mentorship, including the mentor's expertise, communication skills, 
                    responsiveness, ability to provide constructive feedback, and overall impact on mentees' growth and development.
                </p>
                <p>
